cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR

This paper deals with object detection and pose estimation from visual data, which are both topics related to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a method to deal with uncertainty, which is a common problem in robotics and control systems, suggesting that it could also fit in the cs.RO (Robotics) category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to predict multiple outcomes, which could be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. Finally, the paper deals with the geometry of objects, which could be relevant to the cs.GR (Graphics) category.
